Food is very good, nice atmosphere, great for groups or eating alone. Current wait staff need more training and should be more attentive.
I just love this place. I was in town for a job nearby. Did a Google search and BAM there it was.  The homemade treats are fabulous as well. Very comfy and inviting place!

One of my favorite morning stops if I'm wanting to treat myself. I personally like to go on Tuesday's and Thursdays for breakfast burritos! I love that she has a variety of teas as well. There are always a few baked goodies available and is different all the time. The owner is always kind; it's a very relaxed environment that I love going to before I start my work day. I always highly recommend this spot to others.
Wonderful atmosphere, friendly staff that take the time to get to know their customers. Also a remarkably impressive variety of available flavors.

I did not expect to find a coffee shop like Flip Side so far out from Chicago. Very happy I checked them out while in town for a project! Ended up returning several times during my stay because I liked it so much.

There aren't many coffee shops like Flip Side in the region, so give them a shot! I highly recommend taking advantage of their large offerings of Dark Matter coffees!
Great coffee, great homemade snacks and treats. Awesome people! Perfect atmosphere, I could hang out there for hours.

The waitress that was working on My Birthday  March 16th was amazing. She balanced all the tables served drinks took togo orders and cashed everyone out as well. It was a full house as it was our last night of dining out during this virus outbreak! Thank you a d please go have the Husky fries and some wings and pizza garlic cheese bread is fire!!

Ordered at 735pm and recieved my food at 920pm..called 3 times, 840pm driver left 5 min ago.  Called again at 855pm driver ran out of gas,. (Driver had no clue what i was talking about when he got here) 920pm food finally got here.. WILL NEVER ORDER FROM THERE AGAIN.. FRIES WERE BURNT, CHICKEN HAD WAY TO MUCH SAUCE. AND THEY PUT MY BREAD STICK IN THE MAC N CHEESE WHICH WAS WRAPPED IN ALUMINUM FOUL..SOAKED IN CHEESE..

I wish I could give negative stars. The owners and managers are as rude as the employees. I ordered and paid for wings and they were out so they delivered nuggets. How on earth is that acceptable. When I asked for my money back I got told I would get no refund for their sheer stupidity and ignorance and told to not order there again. If you want good friendly service with the food you ordered I wouldn’t eat here.

Ordered for delivery and they couldn’t find my house. Then when we get there all of a sudden it changed to he knocked and no one answered. Weird, my dog didn’t even bark like he does 100% of the time.

Kind of a weird atmosphere. Everyone collects near the door because of the gambling machines. The sign on the front of the building is practically invisible and the place always appears closed even when they're open. The pizza is good though. They have some unique specialty pizzas and the prices are decent. Not a great beer selection but you can usually find something to suit your tastes.

The drinks were great, the food was great. Limited seating, was pretty busy. Seems like a popular townie spot. Interesting Irish pub with a mostly mexican-themed menu. Was well taken care of and would go back again.

This place is amazing.  Wish i would have went sooner.  All food was amazing.  Biggest burrito of my life. I can't wait to go back and try something else.  If you're hungry make sure you try this place.
Best fish tacos ever! Guac is amazing. Margaritas are the bomb! Staff was awesome. Only area that needs improvement is the size of the place. If they expanded, itd be perfect!

Good Mexican fare overall. I like the enchiladas, the burritos not so much. Chips and salsa will run you an extra $2.50 but they are worth it. Full bar.Seating is a little tight for a bigger guy like me and the place is always busy.

Extremely crowded. The front door kept opening and letting in a massive Breeze. Not impressed with paying $40 for a meal for two and eating off of Styrofoam plates that kept melting on to our food. The system there is completely screwed up you have to go up to the bar to pay after you've had your meal and wait for the bartenders who are busy making drinks for the whole establishment in order to pay. Our drinks sat empty  the majority of the time and asked for extra chips which were forgotten. They also ONLY take cash or check and that is not visibly posted when you come in.  Not impressed.

Our order was wrong. out appetizer forgotten until last minute, 1 meal was under cooked, no napkins, no silverware, no working facilities in the mens bathroom, or waitress never checked on us, service was horrible. when we complained I got a thumbs up.

I would not recommend. We had poor service from a very  unattentive waitress. We had to ask for everything from silverware to napkins, and my wife didn't get the dinner she ordered. Not to mention that both of the facilities in the men's room were out of order.

Every time I have been there the food was fantastic. The owner David, would come and chat to see how everything was.  Very comfortable place to sit and enjoy great Mexican food.  We plan on continuing to give them our service.
Good food and ther  apart of my family.
The fish tacos are the best...and the coffee cakes are so so good
The food is always a home run. I meant to take a picture of my food but I always devour it as soon as it comes to the table. Great customer service and REAL food  for a great price.
The food is absolutely amazing. Some of the best food you will find in these small towns.
The food is great! Best place to eat lunch
Food was amazing! It was our first visit. My wife had the house Burger and I had chicken??, five star service and five star food. We will be back..
Cheap drinks great food & service

The food is always amazing. I'm not sure why people complaining about the time are relevant because sometimes perfection takes time. Been out of town for a long time and always have to stop here for food.

They took 45 minutes to make a medium pizza and when I got it it was cold,unseasoned and was charged $12-$13 for it. Which is reasonable.
Not very impressed if your wanting a good pizza that is worth the money make a homemade one! Or get a frozen one.
I ate 2 pieces and I am sick!

So-so service, so-so pizza. Not great not bad. 25 minutes for pizza pickup when told it was 20, whixh is reasonable. Pizza was a bit salty, but good balance of crust/sauce/cheese. Not a super nice/clean feeling interior, so takeout may be your best bet. 3/5 is fair, but with other pizza place close by, you may be best served elsewhere.

I was highly disappointed with service. I ordered a large amount of pizza for a bigger group of people and had it delivered. When the order came one of our pizzas was incorrectly made, we called and was only offered a "discount" on the exact kind of pizza. Over all pizza was lacking toppings and very thinly made.
The staff is very friendly and the food was amazing. I come here often

Great service & plenty of food. Keep in mind what this place is. You're not gonna get gourmet food here but what you do get it is delicious, especially the fried chicken. The staff are wonderful & go out of their way to make your experience great. Plus, my kids love the game room.
I've only been here a couple of times but enjoyed it both times. The most recent time they didn't have the chicken and I was disappointed. But the pizza (plus) buffet is wonderful!
The chicken is very good!  There is something for everyone! You can make special requests for pizza styles.  The staff are friendly and helpful.
Buffets always make me nervous but the food here has been very good quality and I've had no complaints whatsoever.  Fried chicken was great!

It's a nice place for a quick bit to eat and the place is way better than what your expectation might be. All the other food items from the fried chicken to the mashed potatoes, all hit the spot. A must try if you're in the area and you're looking to entertain kids!

At the time of this posting, they only took cash or check. No credit or debit cards are accepted. The ATM was out of service that day, too. I went there for breakfast. Eggs, bacon, pancakes, & coffee tasted pretty good. No issues with service, the place was clean, and staff was very nice.
Food is always good. Fast service. Same ladies waitressing for years. Good place to eat with the family or alone.
Asked to have aluminum foil placed under food because foam cartons melted  into food on previous orders. It didn't get done and the eggs were runny, we wont be back.
Great food. Only four stars because you can't use plastic.
We had breakfast and it was very good.  The service was also good.
Great food & service, we will definitely be back!
Nice time good wedding had fun
First time going there since the late 90s when I was a  dishwasher there. Everything was delicious😋✨ thank you! Sloppy Gene's 🙂
Besides having to pay with cash, this a great little hole in the wall. All the locals know and love it. Eat there probably once a week at least.
Love it!  Friendly staff and great food!
May be small and looks like it's right out of the 50's but has the best sandwich of this kind.  Always have to stop in when we visit from WI
Food is good, small menu and very small business.

My wife and I met friends here for dinner on a Friday night. We had reservations but I'm not sure that was necessary. We were greeted by a friendly hostess who showed us to our table. We ordered the ribs with two sides. We each had the glazed carrots and I had the black beans my wife had the mashed potatoes and gravy. Everything was great. We had the chocolate brownie with ice-cream for dessert (must have!). After we finished, we talked for at least another hour. We were there for three hours and NEVER felt rushed. The waitress was helpful but left us alone. It was a wonderful evening with friends. Highly recommend.
The food was awesome. I had a Reuben the husband had the Pulled Pork sandwich with a brisket nacho appetizer. We were stuffed walking out. The service was good as well. I will be returning soon.

I was in town for a quick meeting for work and our vendor brought us here. Everything was great and the food was very impressive. The staff knew the vendor so they had an idea what to get for us. Very open seating and the lighting was about Norm for this type of dinner. The parking can be tricky because of the location. Please give it a try!
Catering services - food was good, but ordered for 35 and got enough meat to feed only 22 people. Expensive for not even feeding everyone. Also, skip the desserts.
The food was good (I had the fish) and prices were reasonable, but I would've preferred an option for a baked potato, or even fries, in place of the chips.
Food and drinks were good. Just wish they would play some music or something while we ate. Otherwise, great experience.

Was chased down in the parking lot by waitress, saying I didn't pay my bill. After I got over the embarrassment, I went back as she flipped hand and said "whatever"so as it turns out she looked at someone else's bill. Just so we are all clear, she never even apologized!
Really impressed, must try the gargantuan pretzel! I did get thirsty a couple of times, but the whole experience was worth the trip!
Clean, inviting, great service. The food is great haven't had a bad meal yet. Good beers on tap. Great lunch spot
Burgers are good, service during the day can run a little slow, but overall a great place for a good, reasonable lunch!

reviews.author_name: Don’t Look In The Mirror, Mrs. Atelophobia
reviews.text: Great food, and honey chicken, chicken lumpia, and rice for my picky kids 😂. Delicious smoothies, and when its busy, the wait is worth it! The waitress' there are nice and its convenient that the bar is connected to but not apart of it. Its very clean and the food is great. Totally recommend it, especially if you have a love for seafood!
Got so much food for such a great price. Wonderful friendly staff. My girls and I had an amazing experience. Will definitely return.
The food is always amazing. I highly recommend the sushi and the pad woon sen.

Never would have guessed I'd have the best Thai food of my life in Rock Falls, Illinois. SO GOOD!
Very friendly service, reasonable prices. The crab rangoons were the best I've ever had. Hawaiian fried rice was delicious as well as the donut dessert. 
Would highly recommend if you're in the area.
Only been here once, but loved every bit of being there

businesses.name: Triple P BBQ
businesses.address: 3312 West Rock Falls Road, Rock Falls

reviews.text: Go there. Was busy as heck this time but still got food in great time. Service was great. Waiter was short guy with a beard. Didn’t wait at all for a drink refill. Food was great. Been there once before and it was great then too. Will go back.

We found this place as we were traveling in the area and the reviews were good so stopped in... so glad we did!  The place is friendly and the food is amazing.. our waitress provided awesome service and was very personable.  They had so many things that sounded good it was hard to pick so we ordered appetizers we never heard of and then 2 of us got the the combo platters, one got the rib eye steak and one got the mac n cheese pulled pork sandwich. Everything was amazing and you get so much food!  I took home my leftovers from the combo and it fed me and my husband again!  This place is on our list to try again!  Highly recommend!

TOP NOTCH. Food, service and atmosphere are all terrific. Had the 3meat combo platter. 1/2 rack ribs, sliced brisket and hot link along with a big mug of beer, HEAVEN. Highest marks to Shane n staff.Just one word of warning, you better be hungry when eating at Triple P. If not you will have plenty for lunch the next day. We brought home half of our food, generous portions. Again, great job Shane n staff.

The Thursday special is pulled pork sandwich so I tried that, and it was pretty good, not enough meat for my liking but still good. Had mac & cheese and fries as my sides and the mac & cheese was very cheesy and creamy 👌
BBQ sauce was good as well. Overall a good experience for a take out order 👍

Briskit was off the hook good. Loved every bite. Cole slaw n corn bread not so much. N those are the easy things to make. I feel like I just spent my money on a bit of awesome brisket. Will go again tho n try other things.

First time there, by chance looking for an open place in Sterling.  Liked the place and waitress.  Rustic cowboy decor. Prime rib w salad bar was $13.95 on Sunday.  We enjoyed our food and will go back for more!

Very good food! I really enjoy there pan fried pork chops, and their fried chicken, just wish their servers where a little friendlier and had a little better service. But there food makes up for their service.

reviews.author_name: Don’t Look In The Mirror, Mrs. Atelophobia
reviews.text: Food is great, fun place to go with family. Has a pool table and great menu options. Employees are very nice and the service is fast

This is the wagon wheel. The bar, lounge, and restaurant in Sterling. My grandmother, Beverly miller used to run this magnificent place of fun, and having a good time. She recently passed away so going there would make the staff and my grandmother very happy. Thank you for choosing The Wagon Wheel lounge and restaurant.

Always a good time
Hot food & cold beer Great waitress.
It was a Day Time visit. To watch a Game. I do not visit in evening grow to young & ? {They do have some great items on their menu}

Loud But friendly and service was prompt. I can taste the alcohol in my drinks. Very nice place,  very large and open. Very nice clean patio area. They have a REAL kitchen and cook your order there in the licensed establishment.

Grew up in Sterling/Rockfalls and moved  to Oklahoma and been a resident for the last 30 plus years. I was actually impressed! Great venue 👍, great staff! Good people to have some fun! Ever in the Rockfalls area and wonder what it's like to party in Oklahoma/Texas, this place is about as close as your gonna get!
Good food, great atmosphere, great entertainment. Highly recommend it.
Its a good place drunk and meet loose people.

Willy's is truly authentic Mexican food bursting with flavor! The lunch buffet is amazing and the staff are so friendly and inviting!! Margaritas are definitely something to experience and so is the Willy's beer in the big mug with tomato juice...forget what it was called but YEOWZA!! 
VIVA LA WILLY'S!
Simple the best Mexican food in the entire Midwest. I've dined at 100's of them and nobody, I mean NOBODY has better chips and salsa. Especially the chips. They also serve Bohemia!!!
It had been at least 10 years since the last visit.  Got the buffet.  Awesome food!
Great place to go. Nice n friendly. Clean n respectful
Great food. Great service. One of my favorites

Al and leda's is a barebones. Pizza restaurant that feels like a Lunch Cafe. They have some pretty tasty food both my daughter and I enjoy going there. . There is a small difference in price between the Sterling and Dixon locations with Dixon being a little more expensive. The menus are slightly different. But the taste and quality and atmosphere the food is the same.
Great pizza,fair prices. Place could use an update but food is fine.
Really good and quaint pizzeria. It's a Mom and Pop shop with over 50 years of history in Dixon.

Great pizza, salads and "cold" beer as always.  Service was terrific.  Pizza came right from oven to table.  Have been going to Al's since they opened their doors in Dec of 1960!!!!!! Their service and product, qualify and customer service has not varied in all that time.  It's as good now as it ever was!!!! I am a regularand proud of it
We love this pizza! Town favorite, great food, great price

The lunch buffet is a must, they have at least 5 different kinds of pizza, a big salad bar, as well as a few types of pasta and of course their homemade bread. If you just get a water the lunch buffet is about $8.50 which is very reasonably priced for the quality of the food and the selection. I make a point to stop every time I'm in town. I will definitely be back!

Seriously? Who is giving this place five stars?! This was quite possibly one of the top ten worst meals I have ever had. The service was awful. They didn't have the beer they were advertising with a giant lighted beer sign. The tomato sauce was so salty and flavorless it was barely edible. The "Italian hamburger" is basically a giant flattened rubbery meatball. The bread was soggy and not toasted, the wait person didn't even ask if I wanted cheese on it or fries. And best of all, it was served at room temperature. I had to chase down our check at the end of the meal. The three of us agreed that it is not on our list of places to eat again. It is a shame because several co-workers said it was good and now I have to report, no, it is not.

Went and picked up a pizza tonight... one of the best I have from Angelo's III. It has been a long time since we ordered from here. We were not satisfied the last time, but, they have redeemed themselves!
Myself and 3 coworkers went here for the lunch buffet. Really good pizza. Have to try the Mac & Cheese pizza, yummy!
Very nice place for children and family for pizza. The waitress was very nice. Very small but a nice buffet all you can eat. Price reasonable.

Whenever I have to head west, I make a special point of stopping by Arthur's for a Work of Art.  Loaded with meat and cheese, warmed up just the right amount.  Perfect every time.  The homemade chocolates are an added bonus.

Best sandwich restaurant ever... and they're everywhere from Dixon to Moline! Whatever sandwich you choose, make sure you get 'the works'. It's better than Jimmy John's & blows Subway out of the water. If you go once, you'll be back again.
Just recently tried Arthur's and found it to be fantastic! I have many friends who told me about Arthur's but I didn't realize how great it is until I experienced it myself! Can't wait to go back!
The food was so yummy. Great pit stop between chicago and home. Quick and easy and very affordable.

I live out of town, but have family in the area and everytime I come home to visit I'd say I eat half of my meals at Arthur's. It is one of the best places in Dixon to get a great sandwich, wonderful soup or a great baked potato!

I ate there today, the pizza definitely reminds me of another pizza place in town (Angelo’s). Very good Garlic Cheese bread. Service was friendly and they were well staffed. It had some cool decor and the prices were very reasonable.

The service was outstanding and our food all came out within a reasonable amount of time (party of 10 people). The pizza was alright, not my favorite but others seemed to like it. The seating at the high top tables and bar weren’t the most comfortable and the lighting could be better, but overall a very nice atmosphere and friendly staff. Thank you Rhawn for reaching out, that means a lot!
I hope you are reading the reviews my pops ordered a pizza tonight. Could have been left in the oven a bit longer it was really doughy. Otherwise not bad sauce and flavor. Just want you to succeed!

Don't bother with the poutine. They need to either completely revamp it or take it off the menu. Everything else was good or had potential. Nice decor though personally I wouldn't want to sit under the piano they have bolted to the wall.

Went there for the first time today, much smaller inside than expected.. very nicely decorated. Received my chicken sandwich with hair! Told waitress, she took it back and brought back new one about 15 minutes later (with wrong cheese). By that time, my friend was already done eating. Bill was calculated wrong (extra Italian beef added onto our bill). No apology or discount for delay of food and being served hair. Definitely overpriced. $10 for chicken sandwich, no fries or any side.

Visiting the area and found this spot as a place to stop and relax. I had a mocha and muffin; both were good tasting. The service and atmosphere were excellent. The cashier was new to the job but the other workers were friendly and helpful with helping her learn the ropes. I would recommend this spot for anyone looking for a quiet spot to hang out.
Oh my goodness, the sandwich I ordered was very good and the muffins were amazing. I look forward to eating some of the other items. Thanks Margie!

My family and I are new to the area and have been looking for a good bakery. Looks like we found exactly what we were looking for. Stopped in this morning and ordered a few breakfast sandwiches and was blown away. Great experience!
Margie and her staff do a great job, if you want high octane coffee this is the place.
All I can say is it's a regular stop...great coffee.

Stopped with a friend on Thursday for lunch. We arrived at 11:30am the place already had a few tables with people. We were led to our table by our hostess/waitress, she ask for our drink order. She brought us our drinks and took our order. We had a lasagna and spaghetti with marinara sauce with two good size meatballs. The portions were huge, we immediately ask for take home boxes. The lasagna was very filling with good flavor, meaty, the sauce was great. My partner said the spaghetti was great, the marinara sauce was excellent. We had coffee after dinner good coffee.
Our waitress was great. Atmosphere was great. This was my first time there, and I love it.  Had the chicken alfredo special, and the portion was huge. I'd recommend it.
Nice cozy Italian restaurant. Food is great and do are the drinks. A little pricey but worth it.
This place has the best pasta in the area. The prices are affordable. Your plates are customizable. Go with the vodka sauce.
Have eaten there many times, food is always great, you’re not rushed and the cook has cooked off menu a couple times for us . Great ambiance, music and staff. Truly a great place in a small town .

The best chicken in town large pieces of chicken cooked to perfection.. Never had a bad meal ! Mike and Jen and the rest of the Clan are great bunch...
It Dixon little secret soon to be famous 😳🎉🎊
Greatest fish and chicken. Awesome   my only place I really enjoy to eat out at. Always friendly service

BBY has been around longer than I can remember. That being said, I remember it being better. The chicken strips, in my opinion, are too oversized for the light batter that is on them. For the price, the portions are good but the flavors are lacking.
The food was great, you're treated like family and you feel like you are in your own home. The service was excellent, they are very polite
Formerly from Dixon.  Better than Candlelight by miles!  Stop in every time I'm through!  My family's favorite for sure!

Arrived on a very busy Saturday night during an exhibition by an artist. Surprisingly, we were able to find a table quickly even though there were six of us. A short wait at the bar for drinks got us some delicious martinis and mixed drinks. 
Nice place for an elegant drink with friends. Definitely will return!
Nice place good and friendly people to help you pick wine of your choice
Great place,  amazing service and plenty if choices!

I'll change it to four stars. It's a nice place and appreciate the uniqueness. The staff was very friendly and polite. I only gave an okay review because it's not really my thing. My friend and I split the cost and together spent 7$ for four pieces of chocolate.  ???
A beautiful place for our wine and yoga event. Open and airy, art pieces on the brick walls. Martini menu.

Food was good. Waited 15 mins for frozen order though.  Not enough counter help for a busy lunch rush. 
1st time it’s been like this. Normally more efficient.

Great place, friendly staff, clean, a variety of foods items. A step above most fast food places. Great tasting custard with a special flavor each day.
Sometimes can be little slow in the drive thru but this is at busier times of the day.
One of the faster Culvers. Line moved fast. Food came out fast and was very good.

Never order a turtle sundaes at Dixon Culver's.  If you want a good one and your money's worth go to Culvers Rock Falls. 
Two bad experiences is two too many.
Had an order that was misplaced, called and had it situated. The staffing there was amazing. I was treated more than fairly. Definitely will be going back again for more business.

Delicious ice cream and frozen yogurt. They have soft serve ice cream and hard ice cream. You have a choice of many different types of flurries, sundaes, cones and milkshake. They have other specialties like brownie with ice cream, strawberry shortcake and fresh fruit slushy and much more for great prices. Best place for ice cream!!
Very good. However had to wait about 20 min. Too busy.
This place has good real lemonade slush in the summer good icecream to .

What else can I say? Dairy Delite is the Bomb! Try an old fashion banana split, you won't be disappointed!!❤ Only 4 stars cause, depending on time of day, you might have to wait in line, but it'll be well worth the wait..
The food was good. The store was clean. The service decent. But the person at the host station was agitated by everything and made it well known that customers were an inconvenience.

Nicely maintained location. We had the lunch buffet which had a nice selection of items for $8.75. When we visited, it was buy one,get one free which included your drink! 2 buffets with drinks for $9.25 total!

So bad! They cant even take an order right! This is the 3rd time I've ordered for a private event and all were wrong!! I ordered today, and wrong!!!

I don't live in state, but I've eaten here many times over the years when visiting family. The staff is so kind and attentive. I generally order the steak, but the seafood is also fabulous! If you're looking for a great night out with great food, this is a great choice!
Super family friendly.  Great value.  Try the salad bar and chicken tenders. Family run business that has been around forever because they work hard and provide great service and value.
It's decent food for average restaurant prices.  The waiters are polite and prompt.  Not a bad spot to dine in.
Very good food. Had an amazing waiter. Would come back in a heart beat. Steak and shrimp was amazing
It is a nice place with a great salad bar. The service was excellent. Not a fan of their chicken but that is probably just me. The steaks were very good

Just got 2 sandwiches from Jimmy John's drive thru. Price is great, all sandwich ingredients are fresh,  the customer service is outstanding!! The problem I have is the freshness of the bread. The bottom part of the sandwich was extremely hard on both sandwiches! Was this yesterdays bread? ☹
They live up to the name of freaky fast delivery. Driver is always polite and food is always outstanding.
Had time to log in to my gmail and write this review, so not so freaky fast. Left them with two stars because I like the bread.
Love the sandwiches from here decent price and love the fast of drive threw but strange delivery area only certain parts of town .
Friendliest service around! Love the bread.

Huge portions! The interior is full of bright colors and a little busy. The food was good, but (at least the enchiladas I got) were not great. Service was friendly, but at lunchtime on a weekday, we had to flag someone down to pay our bill.

Good Americanized Mexican food.
Fish tacos very good and grilled not deep fried. Salsa is homemade and fantastic. Good servers and drinks.
Always clean and friendly environment. Huge menu selection and food is very authentic and large portions. Great place to have lunch or dinner

I've been here a few times for both dine in and carry out due to convenience of location but the last time we were especially disappointed in their wait staff. Good food, very friendly staff, nice atmosphere with comfortable seating. Seating is usually immediate and food comes to the table quickly
The cauliflower crust pizza was tasty and perfectly cooked. I was impressed with the service as it was Christmas Eve when we went. Friendly staff. Good food.

I love, love, love eating here when I visit. They have the best pizza. I went in with my mom for lunch one day and had the lunch buffet. It's very small but you get your money worth. They had 3 different pizzas, chicken tender, onion rings, friend mushrooms, fries, cinnamon bites, potato salad, macaroni salad, salad bar and a few other things to choose from. It was sooo good and the staff was great too.
We just ordered lunch for our employees.  Thank you very much.  We enjoyed it!
They have cauliflower crust pizza!!! And a variety of specialty pizzas. Few beers and great cooks (especially arturuo) ;)
Food is good sit down service is less than desirable.
Had a small cheese pizza, easy sauce and a well done fry. The pizza was excellent and the fries were beautiful!! Will order from Maria's again. Thank you!
One of the best pizza places in Dixon. Affordable and with great specials.

Is there any good pizza in Dixon? This pizza taste like it has cardboard in it through the cheese can only be eaten with a mouth full of sharks teeth it is that shui. Definitely cheap imitation mozzarella
Messed up my pizza and the boy that was apparently in charge that night was a little smart alek when i picked up my food and when i called in
Great food decent prices all ways have great specials all ways ask what they are !

The food is almost always hot and freshly made. It is a nice spot to hang out of your not being to loud. The workers are respectful and polite, and they try to keep  tables clean as for the restrooms.

First I would  like to say I have been in to this McDonald's as a Doordash Driver and as a customer. This crew day or night has there store running  like a well oiled  machine. Even when there is a problem  they stay calm and handle everything  very professionally. I have been In their drive up many times 2 full rows of cars. I have never been in line more than 5 minutes. I would like to point out how friendly the service is here due to the conversation I had with multiple employees and even 1 of the owners. Clean and caring service seems to be a couple of their goals cause without a doubt that is exactly what I've experienced multiple times visiting their establishment.
It's Lent and fish fillet are 2 for $5.  Great price as regular price is rather high.  Prepared well and ff we're good.

We stopped here on a 13 hour road trip with the kids because they have a play place, and we will definitely be making it a regular road trip stop, even though it’s a few miles off the highway. Everything was super clean and all employees seemed to care and be engaged in their jobs. Team was very accommodating and got my special order food perfectly. It was such a great experience. First time I’ve ever reviewed a fast food restaurant; It was that great!
The food is always good, moderately priced for the amount you get. Your order is ready usually  fairly quickly and very fresh. Large space for bigger groups if needed.
Nice local place for Mexican food. Chips and salsa are tasty. Love the white sauce for the chips. Decent prices too
Superb service! The staff was so friendly and service was exceptional. The food was delicious and plentiful. The menu had a large selection.

Chips for salsa were straight out of a bag. It's a Mexican Restaurant and kinda expected fresh made chips. The portions were big and prices not bad. Would I go again yes, but only if my favorite spot was closed

I'm sold on this place! We have tried every Mexican restaurant in the Lee and Ogle County area and greatly disappointed.... until today! I had the chili Colorado and my wife had the chili Verde and both dishes were delicious! Since moving from New Mexico and the reservation we have been trying to find a real Southwest cuisine. The closest we found was Fiesta Cancun in Rockford, IL 55 miles away, or Jalapenos in Peru, IL 35 miles away. Mr. Tequilas has a very diverse menu with maybe 100 or more dishes to choose from. We just might go broke attempting to try every item! The portions are generous, their variety of sauces incomparable. Very nice atmosphere, polite and cordial wait staff and very competitive prices. If you want REAL Mexican cuisine you won't be disappointed with Mr.Tequilas! Definitely will return again...and again!

Our waitress was great! She's fun and provided good service. Nice atmosphere. The garbage pail fries were really good. My chicken wrap was so-so. Most of the rest of our group enjoyed their food. Would go again and try something different.

A great place to hang out. The place was jumping on Sunday afternoon around 1PM. There were three of us; we had the BLT, the Cuban and pulled pork with fries. The food was great & everyone was happy. The only thing that was not so great was the service. And, honestly I think that is because the wait person had too many tables. She was very nice, but I had to chase her down a couple of times and we ran out of beer more than once. All-in-all a great experience and we'll go back.

I highly recommend this BBQ place!! This was our first time here and we were absolutely not disappointed. The food had great flavor, the waiter was friendly, and the food was prepared quickly. We will definitely be back!

The trash can fries are presented in an actual can that the server lifts off once the dish is on the table, and they are a hearty serving of fries topped with pulled pork, cheese, jalapenos and other deliciousness. Great atmosphere. Good selection of regional beers.
I had the Maverick burger with fries. My wife had Chicken George. Very good. Large portions. Plenty  to take home for later. Food was served very quickly. Nice and clean.

This place is amazing!  It is family owned, exceptional food and service!  We are a family of seven and all of us count down the days until we come back.  Our favorite part is the people...the owners and employees are the nicest ever!  We always leave with full bellies and smiles.  This is a true must visit restaurant!  The skillets, sandwiches, and cinnamon roll pancakes are amazing!!!!  You will not be disappointed I promise!

Always very friendly people, delicious food, once the owners know you they greet you by name and talk with you. Newly remodeled, beautiful inside. I had 2 cinnamon roll pancakes that were as big as my plate, they looked and tasted like a cinnamon roll. They even had the icing on it so I didn't even put any syrup on it.

Had 2 eggs scrambled soft,bacon, hashbrowns and whole wheat toast. Very good breakfast for a very reasonable price. Staff was warm and welcoming and didn't disappoint with service. Will definitely return and recommend.

Stopped while touring Dixon on motorcycle. It was about 1 PM. There were 6 of us and were seated promptly. Most ordered sandwiches or fried chicken but I had the cinnamon roll pancake breakfast with scrambled eggs and bacon. Best pancakes ever-unbelievable!! Our server was Pam and service and food was phenomenal!!
Always, always great food here. The owners are very hospitable and the servers/waitresses are always very nice.
First experience at Rockin Nutrition was very welcoming, informative and upbeat! Good vibes all around. Recommended 100%!
Amazing shakes and the owner is super friendly. Try the strawberry banana!! Plus she does FREE fitness classes. Definitely worth trying out
Awesome staff and awesome drinks! Their free classes look like a lot of fun!!
Fantastic service and great drinks.  The Captain America Tea was really good. Highly recommended!
So happy with my visit that I am now a regular customer. Really friendly great smiles through the door. Very helpful and informative of what they're selling. They know there stuff!

An authentic Mexican restaurant with good service, great food, and a friendly staff. We arrived only an hour before they closed and they welcomed us warmly.  My fajita salad was wonderful, almost too much, and spiced just right.. Loved it.
Really enjoyed attending a private party here. Food and the drinks were very good.
Awesome place!  The food was very good and our waitress was excellent!!!  We will definitely be back!
Always fast service and great food. Family-owned. Cash only!!
Always delicious food and very friendly staff

I've heard many good things about the place. On my 1st visit the wrap I had looked and tasted like Carl budding turkey and their home cooked chips were too burnt to eat. I did ask 4 a different batch I was told that's how they're coming out so she did give me fries as a replacement. I plan on going back again maybe it was just an off night. I won't get the wrap thou.
Smoked Prime Rib is different than any place I've every had prime rib if you like prime rib you should give it a try.Friday and Sat Night
Love this place. Excellent food and fast service.
Great food and quick service. I have yet to find anything that they do that I dislike!
Great burgers friendly staff, atmosphere makes you feel welcome.  A little small and crowded but still a great place to have a burger and a beer.

Four of us went for dinner last evening and had a variety of different dishes. Everyone was fairly pleased with his/her food selections. The service was good despite the fact the restaurant was packed and there were no open tables. The bar was crowded as well. Pretty much, people were being turned away at the door. So, I highly recommend reservations. I would have given this five stars except for one thing: My mate ordered the beef pad Thai, and there was very little meat in the dish. One item of note: Elliott, the bartender and manager, is extraordinarily easy on the eyes. We will be returning, no doubt.

The Jewel of Dixon, Somkit (Touch of Thai).  Thanks to the wonderful service and fantastic sushi chefs the evening was a great success.  First impressions of the immediate greeting with a smile, soothing atmosphere, well thought out seating floor plan and liquor counter placement were perfect.  Drink options were plentiful, and food options not overwhelming.  A perfect balance of food.  The Pad Woonsen was flavorful and executed to perfection.  Tropical Roll was a sublime balance of fish to rice with the sauces delicately drizzled atop.  The presentation was well done with the placement of the garnish as to not be in the way but a subtle reminder of what was in front. From the light exposure to the black marble counter and intriguing design of the interior with the use of iron piping and light color wood shelving, a great touch of rustic class.  Elliot(t) and the Somkit service family presented an evening to remember and return to, hungry for more.

The best Thai place (and eatery in general) in the Sterling/Dixon area. Good food at reasonable prices. I had been there numerous times, most recently for the Saturday lunch buffet in the picture. The food is always tasty and the staff attentive and friendly. A "go-to" for the area!

One of very few top-notch sit-down restaurants in the area. The sushi is very good, definitely rivals some metropolitan sushi bars. Top recommendations on the menu are seaweed salad, spicy fried rice, crazy noodles, salmon skin maki, the Tropical, and their Thai iced tea. Oh, and if you feel adventurous, ask for a special sushi off the menu call The Inappropriate. You won't be dissapointed!
Love the food it is so great, and the sushi taste amazing and fresh.  The atmosphere is really inviting and always had good service. Highly recommend this place.

To go beef place with great pulled pork. Combo Italian sausage and Polish was typical for a “Vienna beef” place. Friendly and quick 5 minutes and out the door. Clearly a Chicago themed establishment with Bears photos and signs.  
Had pizza by the slice ready to go in a warmer but didn’t see any takers. Thin to medium thick crust.

Very limited counter seating for 8.

A hidden Paradise with true old school Chicago food tradition. What to experience what food should taste like stop in try a dog and Fry's or a real Italian beef.  Thank you Gina who I believe was name of the wonderful woman working, for opening up a great spot to grab some food and sit by the river and enjoy good food

There gyros are spectacular and so filling. Love this joint!!! And no readers I didn't smoke before going, saved that for after. I'm playing. Or am i???? Either way, sow belly's will be my fav gyro place!!!!

Food and Price's A+; 5 stars for what is descripted

Not a sit down restaurant.
Less than a "fine dining experience."

On a side note, the breaded mushrooms were battered in breading that reminded me of fried oysters I suppose. They were the best mushrooms I have had. 

What you see is what you get and you can't beat the prices. Everything is flavored well and it definitely has the "Chicago Dawg" feel and taste. 

A high class hot dog at best, but worth the drive and dime.
Great hole in the wall joint for Chicago style food. It can be a little hit or miss sometimes but it's easy to forgive them because when they hit they knock it out of the park.

This is a typical Subway restaraunt. The food is good, the staff is polite and helpful. It's a good place to go for a quick sandwich at a great value.

We were asked what we wanted,  my husband asked for wheat bread, nope they didn't have any. We did have time to look around as we waited for service, one of the dirtiest shops I've been in. The glass around the food was covered in dried food. We didn't eat, very happy that we drove to the Subway near the high school on Everett.  We felt welcome at this Subway.  Subway is kinda like McDonald's, when you are traveling, you can count on them for good, clean facilities and consistent food. Except the Subway by the interstate, inside Road Ranger, in Dixon, Illinois
